silver; half fluted almost spherical body standing on three scroll legs, with wood handle

Silver; the small body is almost spherical.  The lower half is fluted; above this is a narrow band of matting and an applied moulded girdle.  The short beak-like spout has a heart-shaped opening.  The hinged cover is flat and gadrooned, and has a acorn-shaped finial.  The jug stands on three scroll legs with fleur-de lis, scroll and flower capitals.  The wooden handle is set at 100 degrees to the body.  Opposite the handle is engraved a coat-of-arms.
